tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE Product (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
manufacturing_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE TestResult (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
product_id INT NOT NULL,
test_date DATE NOT NULL,
result VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE TestDetails (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
test_result_id INT NOT NULL,
test_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
test_value VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE TestLimits (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
test_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
min_value DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
max_value DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE products (
    product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name VARCHAR(255),
    product_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE test_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT,
    test_date DATE,
    test_result VARCHAR(50),
    test_engineer VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE test_methods (
    method_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    method_name VARCHAR(100),
    method_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE product_quality (
    quality_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT,
    test_id INT,
    quality_score DECIMAL(5,2),
    pass_status BOOLEAN
)

CREATE TABLE test_engineers (
    engineer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    engineer_name VARCHAR(100),
    engineer_email VARCHAR(255)
)
